check_end_date_is_after_start_date
	attempt the following
		check if end year is greater than start year
			return that data is not dodgy and causes no error
		otherwise check if end year is less than start year
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if end month is greater than start month
			return that data is not dodgy and causes no error
		otherwise check if end month is less than start month
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if end day is greater than start day
			return that data is not dodgy and causes no error
		otherwise check if end day is less than start day
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if end hour is greater than start hour
			return that data is not dodgy and causes no error
		otherwise check if end hour is less than start hour
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if end minute is greater than start minute
			return that data is not dodgy and causes no error
		otherwise check if end minute is less than start minute
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if end second is greater than start second
			return that data is not dodgy and causes no error
		otherwise check if end second is less than start second
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise the start and end times are identical
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
	run if any error occurred
		return that data is dodgy and causes an error


check_trip_time_speed_and_distance
	attempt the following
		check if trip duration multiplied by speed is between 90% and 150% of the listed trip distance
			if it is return that data is not dodgy and causes no error
			otherwise return that data is dodgy but causes no error
	run if any error occurred
		return that data is dodgy and causes an error


check_date_exists
	attempt the following
		check if start year or end year is zero as year zero does not exist
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if start and end months are both between 1 and 12 inclusive
			return that data is not dodgy and causes no error
		otherwise check if start month is april june september or november
			check if start day is less than 1 or greater than 30
				return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if end month is april june september or november
			check if end day is less than 1 or greater than 30
				return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if start or end month is february and the day is outside the range of 1 to 29
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if start day is the 29th of february
			call check leap year on the start date field
				if it is not a leap year return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if end day is the 29th of february
			call check leap year on the end date field
				if it is not a leap year return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise check if either start or end day is less than 1 or greater than 31
			return that data is dodgy but causes no error
		otherwise
			return that data is not dodgy and causes no error
	run if any error occurred
		return that data is dodgy and causes an error


check_leap_year
	check if the year in the given date field is greater than zero
		check if year is not a multiple of 4 using div error checker
			return false as it is not a leap year
		otherwise check if year is not a multiple of 100
			return true as it is a leap year
		otherwise check if year is a multiple of 400
			return true as it is a leap year
	otherwise year is before year 1 CE so add 1 to compensate for missing year zero
		print a message noting the unusual year
		check if year plus one is not a multiple of 4 using div error checker
			return false as it is not a leap year
		otherwise check if year plus one is not a multiple of 100
			return true as it is a leap year
		otherwise check if year plus one is a multiple of 400
			return true as it is a leap year


div_error_checker
	attempt the following
		divide numerator by denominator
		cast result to an integer, which will error if result is not a whole number
		return false to indicate no error and that numerator is a multiple of denominator
	run if any error occurred
		return true to indicate an error and that numerator is not a multiple of denominator


