	get total visits to each station by adding array of times started at to array of times ended at
	set an array of end stations and the array of times each station was ended at to the output of a sort parallel arrays function where the inputs are the array of stations and the number of times each station was ended at
	set an array of start stations and the array of times each station was started at to the output of a sort parallel arrays function where the inputs are the array of stations and the number of times each station was started at
	return the number of stations, total visits to each station, array of stations, number of times each station was started at, stations array sorted to match start station tally, number of times each station was ended at, stations sorted to match that


bubble_sort_parallel_arrays
	set boolean tracking if the array is sorted to false
	while array is not sorted
		set sorted boolean to true
		loop through the number array up to the second to last element
			check if the value at the current position is greater than the next value
				swap current and next values in the number array
				swap current and next values in the info array
				set sorted boolean to false
	return the sorted info array and the sorted number array


analyse_filter_data
	set total journeys to the number of data entries
	set minimum trip duration to the first duration entry
	set maximum trip duration to the first duration entry
	set total trip duration to the first duration entry
	set minimum trip distance to the first distance entry
	set maximum trip distance to the first distance entry
	set total trip distance to the first distance entry
	loop through every trip entry after the first
		check if this duration is less than the current minimum
			update minimum trip duration
		otherwise check if this duration is greater than the current maximum
			update maximum trip duration
		check if this distance is less than the current minimum
			update minimum trip distance
		otherwise check if this distance is greater than the current maximum
			update maximum trip distance
		add this duration to the total trip duration
		add this distance to the total trip distance
	divide total duration by total journeys to find average trip duration
	divide total distance by total journeys to find average trip distance
	return total journeys, minimum duration, maximum duration, average duration, minimum distance, maximum distance, average distance


